<div class="container">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>ConocoPhillips (COP) Intrinsic Value Estimate</h1>
    <p class="lede">A transparent, step-by-step discounted cash flow valuation of ConocoPhillips. We use actual financial data to arrive at a single fair value estimate for COP shares.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="vc-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="vc-label">Current Price</div>
        <div class="vc-value">${currentPrice.toFixed(2)}</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="vc-label">Intrinsic Value</div>
        <div class="vc-value accent">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="vc-label">Margin of Safety</div>
        <div class="vc-value" style={`color: ${marginOfSafety > 0 ? '#10b981' : '#ef4444'}`}>{marginOfSafety > 0 ? '+' : ''}{marginOfSafety}%</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="vc-verdict" style={`background-color: ${verdictColor}20; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}50;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Methodology & Assumptions</h2>
  <p>We use a two-stage Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model. This involves forecasting Free Cash Flow (FCF) for the next 5 years, calculating a terminal value for all years after, and discounting those cash flows back to today's present value.</p>

  <div class="assumptions-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Required return based on the 10Y Treasury ({ (treasuryYield * 100).toFixed(2) }%) plus an equity risk premium suitable for the energy sector.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-label">FCF Growth (Y1-5)</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Conservative growth rate reflecting a mature E&P business and long-term commodity cycles.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-label">Terminal Growth</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Assumes long-term growth slightly below GDP, acknowledging the eventual energy transition.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Cash Flow Projections</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>Projected FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>Discount Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">Base (TTM)</td>
          <td>${Math.round(fcf2024).toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>-</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left">Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(3)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3" style="text-align:left">Present Value of Years 1-5</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Enterprise to Equity Value</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">PV of FCF (Years 1-5)</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td style="text-align:left">Enterprise Value</td>
          <td>${enterpriseValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">Plus: Cash & Equivalents</td>
          <td>${Math.round(cashAndInvestments).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">Less: Total Debt</td>
          <td>${Math.round(totalDebt).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td style="text-align:left">Equity Value</td>
          <td>${Math.round(equityValue).toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">Shares Outstanding (Diluted)</td>
          <td>{Math.round(sharesOutstanding).toLocaleString()} M</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td style="text-align:left">Intrinsic Value Per Share</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Financial Track Record</h2>
  <p>Historical performance provides a reality check for our forward projections.</p>

  <h3>Revenue ($B)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {revenueHistory.length > 0 ? revenueHistory.map(r => (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill revenue" style={`width: ${Math.max(5, (r.value / Math.max(...revenueHistory.map(h => h.value))) * 100)}%`}>
            ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(1)}B
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    )) : <p>Data unavailable.</p>}
  </div>

  <h3>Free Cash Flow ($B)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {fcfHistory.length > 0 ? fcfHistory.map(r => (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill fcf" style={`width: ${Math.max(5, (r.value / Math.max(...fcfHistory.map(h => h.value))) * 100)}%`}>
            ${(r.value / 1000).toFixed(1)}B
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    )) : <p>Data unavailable.</p>}
  </div>

  <h3>Earnings Per Share (Diluted)</h3>
  <div class="bar-chart">
    {epsHistory.length > 0 ? epsHistory.map(r => (
      <div class="bar-row">
        <div class="bar-label">{r.year}</div>
        <div class="bar-track">
          <div class="bar-fill eps" style={`width: ${Math.max(5, (r.value / Math.max(...epsHistory.map(h => h.value))) * 100)}%`}>
            ${r.value.toFixed(2)}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    )) : <p>Data unavailable.</p>}
  </div>

  <h3>Margin Trends</h3>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>Operating Margin</th>
          <th>Profit Margin</th>
          <th>FCF Margin</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {marginHistory.length > 0 ? marginHistory.map(m => (
          <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left">{m.year}</td>
            <td>{m.operating}%</td>
            <td>{m.profit}%</td>
            <td>{m.fcfMargin}%</td>
          </tr>
        )) : <tr><td colspan="4">Data unavailable.</td></tr>}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
  <p>Intrinsic value is highly sensitive to the discount rate and growth assumptions. The highlighted cell represents our base case.</p>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="sensitivity-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Discount Rate ↓ / Growth →</th>
          {sensitivityGrowth.map(g => (
            <th class={Math.abs(g - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>{(g * 100).toFixed(0)}%</th>
          ))}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {sensitivityTable.map(row => (
          <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left">{(row.dr * 100).toFixed(0)}%</td>
            {row.values.map((v, i) => (
              <td class={Math.abs(row.dr - discountRate) < 0.001 && Math.abs(sensitivityGrowth[i] - growthRatePhase1) < 0.001 ? 'current' : ''}>
                ${v}
              </td>
            ))}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>What This Model Doesn't Capture</h2>
  <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Sustained High Oil Prices:</strong> If geopolitical tensions or supply constraints keep crude prices elevated over the long term, FCF will significantly outpace our 5% growth assumption.</li>
    <li><strong>Accretive M&A:</strong> Successful integration of acquisitions (like Marathon Oil) could unlock massive synergies and boost free cash flow generation.</li>
    <li><strong>Aggressive Share Buybacks:</strong> ConocoPhillips returns significant capital to shareholders. Fewer outstanding shares over time naturally increase the per-share value beyond static projections.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Commodity Price Crashes:</strong> A structural decline in oil demand due to macroeconomic recession or rapid EV adoption would severely compress cash flows and margins.</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory Pressures:</strong> Stricter environmental regulations, carbon taxes, or restricted drilling access could escalate costs and strand assets.</li>
    <li><strong>Capital Allocation Missteps:</strong> Overpaying for acquisitions or overinvesting during peak cycles has historically destroyed shareholder value in the E&P space.</li>
  </ul>

